Iavan Pijoos, News24(File) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Tsianda - A manhunt is underway for a group of suspects after a man was found burnt beyond recognition in Tsianda, Limpopo police said on Saturday. Police received information that a group of people were busy assaulting a man on a mountain outside the Tsianda village, Lieutenant Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said.&nbsp; On arrival, the body of a middle-aged man was found burnt and the suspects fled the scene.&nbsp;&nbsp;The incident happened on Friday.&nbsp;The motive remains unknown and no arrests had been made.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.